<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-05T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-05T23:00:00-05:00" n="174" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11061: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-06T12:00:00+08:00">August 6,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 6—10:30
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>670. Legation’s 667, August 5 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>],5 p.m. Following
                            from American Consulate, Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“August 5, 8 p.m. Changsha reported retaken by Ho Chien today.
                                    Six regiments of National reinforcements have arrived Hankow
                                    today, <pb facs="0261" n="163" xml:id="pg_163"/> situation
                                    easier. Admiral [Craven] arrived last night. Three American
                                    gunboats in Hankow.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>